Para"><span data-testid=3D"topicText" class=3D"TopicPara_topicText__CUB0d">=
Chocolate toxicosis does not cause specific lesions. Hyperemia, hemorrhages=
, or congestion of multiple organs may occur as agonal changes. Severe arrh=
ythmias may result in pulmonary edema or congestion. Chocolate or cocoa bea=
n hulls may be present in the GI tract at necropsy.</span></p></div></secti=
